                  ***** FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE *****
 
ASDG ACCEPTING APPLICATIONS FOR ADPRO DEVELOPER STATUS.  BUSINESS
OPPORTUNITIES ABOUND.
 
ASDG, makers of the number one selling Amiga image processing product,
is accepting applications for ADPro developer status.  Using a
comprehensive and proprietary DevKit, developers can tap into a high
profile clientele with opportunities to work with the market leader.
 
Madison WI, June 17, 1992 --- ASDG Incorporated, makers of Art
Department Professional (the number one selling image processing
product for the Commodore Amiga), announce that they are accepting
applications from those individuals and companies wishing to become
ADPro developers.
 
The company has prepared a comprehensive developer kit consisting of
"Autodoc" style documentation and a library which hides much of the
complexity of writing ADPro modules.  Using this kit, a proficient
Amiga programmer can create loader, saver, and operator modules which
will operate correctly with ADPro version 2.
 
If a prospective developer's application is approved, the license to
use the ADPro DevKit will cost $200 and obligates the developer to
meet certain quality benchmarks.  "If a third party module causes a
problem on an end-user's machine, ASDG's name is on the bottom line."
said company president Perry Kivolowitz.  He continued, "We require a
contractual obligation to certain quality standards so that ADPro
owners are assured of getting third party products of the same high
standards that they expect from ASDG."
 
The developer kit does not dictate what structure a business
relationship between ASDG and its developers may assume.  Some
developers may choose to market their products themselves, while
others may opt for a closer relationship, perhaps through a licensing
of their products or an outright purchase by ASDG.
 
Company president Kivolowitz said, "We've looked at the unsuccessful
attempts other companies have made to foster a third party
after-market.  We feel our developer program will succeed because of
the side of our installed base, the quality of our developer
materials, our willingness to take a direct hand in promoting some
third party products to our installed base, and our quality commitment
contract."
 
To request an ADPro developer application, or to learn more about
ADPro and ASDG's other color imaging solutions, contact Gina Cerniglia
at ASDG Incorporated, 925 Stewart Street, Madison, WI 53713 or call
(608) 273-6585.
 
Art Department Professional is a registered trademark of ASDG
Incorporated.  Amiga is a registered trademark of Commodore-Amiga,
Inc.
